# Accessibility Rules

Every UI component must meet basic accessibility standards.
Accessibility is not optional — it is part of the definition of done.

## Forms

- Every input MUST have a `<label>` with `htmlFor` matching the input `id`
- Use shadcn `<Label>` component (never raw `<label>` without it)
- Error messages MUST be linked via `aria-describedby`
- Required fields MUST have `aria-required="true"` or `required` attribute
- Disabled fields MUST have `disabled` attribute (not just visual styling)

```tsx
// Correct
<div>
  <Label htmlFor="email">Email</Label>
  <Input
    id="email"
    type="email"
    aria-describedby={error ? "email-error" : undefined}
    aria-required="true"
  />
  {error && <p id="email-error" className="text-destructive text-sm mt-1">{error}</p>}
</div>
```

## Buttons and Interactive Elements

- Every `<button>` MUST have visible text OR `aria-label` if icon-only
- `IconButton` (icon-only) MUST always have `aria-label`
- Links that open in a new tab MUST have `aria-label` or `target="_blank"` with visible indicator
- Buttons that trigger async actions MUST have `aria-busy` and `disabled` during loading

```tsx
// Icon-only button
<Button variant="ghost" size="icon" aria-label="Delete item">
  <Trash2 size={16} />
</Button>

// Loading state
<Button disabled={isLoading} aria-busy={isLoading}>
  {isLoading ? 'Saving...' : 'Save'}
</Button>
```

## Images

- Every `<Image>` MUST have a descriptive `alt` attribute
- Decorative images MUST have `alt=""`
- Never omit `alt` — TypeScript will catch it, but be intentional

## Navigation and Landmarks

- Pages MUST have a `<main>` element wrapping the primary content
- Use semantic HTML: `<nav>`, `<header>`, `<footer>`, `<section>`, `<article>` where appropriate
- Never use `<div>` or `<span>` for elements that have semantic equivalents

## Focus Management

- All interactive elements MUST be keyboard-accessible (reachable via Tab)
- Use `focus-visible:` Tailwind variants, never remove focus outlines entirely
- Modals and dialogs MUST trap focus when open (shadcn Dialog handles this)
- After closing a modal, focus MUST return to the trigger element

```tsx
// Never do this
className="outline-none"  // removes all focus indicators

// Do this instead
className="focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-accent-primary"
```

## Color and Contrast

- Never convey information with color alone (use icons or text too)
- Error states must show both a color change AND an icon or text
- Don't rely solely on `text-text-secondary` for important content — it may fail contrast

## ARIA

- Use `role` only when semantic HTML is not enough
- Common roles: `role="alert"` for dynamic error messages, `role="status"` for live updates
- `aria-live="polite"` for non-critical updates, `aria-live="assertive"` for errors

```tsx
// Dynamic error that appears after action
<p role="alert" aria-live="assertive" className="text-destructive">
  {errorMessage}
</p>
```

## Checklist before finishing any component

- [ ] All inputs have visible labels
- [ ] All interactive elements are keyboard accessible
- [ ] Icon-only buttons have `aria-label`
- [ ] Images have meaningful `alt` text
- [ ] Error messages are programmatically associated (`aria-describedby`)
- [ ] Loading states disable buttons and set `aria-busy`
- [ ] Focus rings are visible (never removed globally)
